## 🛑🛑🛑 IRON RULE — *(optional — only if you have a sibling fork)*

**Delete this section if this install has no sibling fork on the same machine.**

A `<this-install>` chat NEVER writes to the `<sibling-install>` repo. `<sibling-install>` lives at `<sibling-path>` locally. It is a completely separate project owned by you and evolved through ITS OWN git workflow in separate chats.

What "never writes" means concretely:

- ❌ Don't create files inside `<sibling-path>` from a `<this-install>` chat
- ❌ Don't edit files inside `<sibling-path>` from a `<this-install>` chat
- ❌ Don't delete files inside `<sibling-path>` from a `<this-install>` chat
- ❌ Don't `git` anything against the `<sibling-install>` repo
- ❌ Don't `npm install`, `npm run`, or otherwise modify `<sibling-path>` from a `<this-install>` chat

What IS allowed:

- ✅ READ files in `<sibling-path>` for reference

### pm2 app naming convention

pm2 has ONE daemon per user account; app names must be unique across installs. Use a per-install suffix:

- ✅ `bear-watch-server-<install-suffix>`
- ✅ `paper-trade-bot-<install-suffix>`

### Five-layer isolation between sibling installs

The dual-bot setup needs FIVE independent layers of isolation:

| Layer | Pattern (this install) |
|-------|------------------------|
| Repo location | `<this-install-path>` vs `<sibling-path>` |
| Runtime data | All under `<this-install-path>/runtime/{bots,lab,config,pm2}/` |
| Env var names | `<INSTALL>_*` prefix on every internal env var |
| pm2 app names | `<role>-<install-suffix>` |
| Scheduled task names | `<INSTALL>-*` prefix |

Plus port isolation: `<this install>=<port-A>`, `<sibling>=<port-B>`.

