## This install's git push policy

*(Pick one — delete the other.)*

**Option A — public fork (Stratos-like):** Default: ask per push. Treat every `git push` as Tier 3 requiring explicit per-push consent typed in chat for THAT specific push. "Restore," "merge," "sync," "ship," etc. do NOT imply push authorization.

**Option B — private local-only (pbxtra-like):** **NEVER push to any remote.** Repo contains confidential trading data; stays on this machine forever. No `git push`, `git pull`, `git fetch`, `git remote add` — ever.

