## Live bot specifics (this install)

*(Delete if no live bot is configured.)*

The live mainnet bot is **`<bot-name>`** (`<strategy-name>` strategy, ~$<X> starting capital). It runs **INSIDE `bear-watch-server-<install-suffix>`**.

**Configuration:**
- Wallet: `<wallet-pubkey>`
- Entry: `<entry-rule>`
- Exit: `<exit-rule>`
- Max hold: `<duration>`
- Pool cap: `$<X>/trade`, `<cooldown>` cooldown

**Implication for safety:** pm2 supervision of `bear-watch-server-<install-suffix>` IS the live bot's restart safety net — pm2 reloads DO affect the live bot. State files at `~/.<install>-bots/state/` persist across reloads. A trade signal arriving during the ~1-2s reload window can be missed. Hence the explicit-consent rule in the framework operational doc at `../CLAUDE.md` ("NEVER stop/restart while open position").

**Current bot-state (holding/flat)** is tracked in `<this-install>/_context/bear-watch/STATUS.md`. Check it before any Tier 1+ edit.

